The draws for this seasons schoolboy  domestic cup competitions were made on Monday evening last (Oct. 24th). All eyes were on the draw for the under 11 cup to see who the holders Ballingarry were paired with. As it happened Ballingarry under 11 will be at home to St. Itas in the first round.

The  1st round draw involving all Ballingarry schoolboy teams is as follows:

Under 10s v Shauntrade (away);
Under 11v v St. Itas (home);
Under 12s v Breska Rovers (home);
Under 13s v A Bye;
Under 14s v Killeaney (home);
Under 15s v Askeaton (away);
Under 16s v Glin Rovers (away).

The dates for these fixtures have yet to be finalised

FAI Junior Cup Draw - Round 2
(Ties to be played the weekend of the 27th/ 28th September)

Clare / Desmond / Kerry:
Sporting Ennistymon Vs Shannon Olympic FC ; Newcastle West Rovers Vs Hermitage FC ; Glin Rovers Vs Askeaton FC ; 
Ruan Utd Vs Rineanna Rovers ; Newmarket Celtic Vs Moher Celtic ; Connolly Celtic Vs Bridge Utd ; Ennis Town Vs Tralee Ath ; 
Carrig Celtic Vs Newcastle West FC ; Tulla Utd Vs Ballysteen FC ; Old Mill FC Vs Abbeyfeale Utd ; Athea Utd Vs Broadford Utd ; 
Mitchels Ave FC Vs Rathkeale Utd ; Spa Road Vs Killeaney FC ; Castleisland Vs St Brendans Park FC ; Ballingarry AFC Vs Shannonside Utd ; Bridge Celtic Vs Mastergeena Utd ; Tralee Dynamos Vs Killarney Celtic ; Killarney Ath Vs Avenue Utd OR St Pats FC ; Listowel Celtic Vs Fenit Saphires ; Dingle Bay Rovers Vs Classic FC

Reidy Cup 1st Round:
Abbeyfeale Utd B V Carrig Celtic B ; Shannonside FC B V Rathkeale B ; Askeaton B V Pallaskenry ; Shountrade V Broadford Utd B ; Feenagh B V Feenagh ; Granagh Utd V Kilcornan ; Ballingarry B V Adare Utd ; Rockhill Rovers V St. Itas ; Breska Rovers V Knockaderry ; Ferry Rangers V Glin Rovers B
Byes for Athea Utd B, Bally Rovers, Creeves Celtic, Glantine Rovers, Kildimo Utd, Newcastle West Rovers B

All games at all levels involving the club were postponed due to the weather.

